CREATE TABLE Orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, order_date DATE, total_amount DECIMAL(10, 2), status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES Customers(customer_id))</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, customer_name, email, phone_number, address) select 1, 'john doe', 'john.doe@example.com', '123-456-7890', '123 abc street'</s>

CREATE TABLE Products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), price DECIMAL(8, 2), stock_quantity INT)</t><s>INSERT INTO Products (product_id, product_name, price, stock_quantity) SELECT 3, 'Product C', 120.00, 75</s>

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 1, 'Alice', 'alice@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 3, 'Charlie', 'charlie@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) select 3, 'charlie', 'charlie@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 4, 'David', 'david@example.com'</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 5, 'Eve', 'eve@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 6, 'Frank', 'frank@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) select 6, 'frank', 'frank@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) select 7, 'grace', 'grace@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 8, 'Hank', 'hank@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 9, 'Ivy', 'ivy@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 12, 'Larry', 'larry@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

<t>CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) select 13, 'mia', 'mia@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 14, 'Nick', 'nick@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

<t>CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) select 15, 'olivia', 'olivia@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 16, 'Paul', 'paul@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 18, 'Rose', 'rose@example.com'</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

<t>CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) select 18, 'rose', 'rose@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>INSERT INTO customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) SELECT 19, 'Sam', 'sam@example.com'</s>

CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))</t><s>insert into customers (customer_id, customer_name, customer_email) select 19, 'sam', 'sam@example.com'</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(50), product_price DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

<t>CREATE TABLE employees (employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY, employee_name VARCHAR(50), employee_department VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE order_items (order_item_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_id INT, product_id INT, quantity INT, FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))

CREATE TABLE orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, order_date DATE, customer_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR(50), customer_email VARCHAR(50))
